Dennis Silver fight was a great match ...very fast paced fight ...

It wasnt a super card by any means, but look at it like this...  Its a German event which is a country they are still trying to break into.... They lost the co-main event of the evening due to illness... and most of all, they were competing with Pacquiao-Margarito which would have beat them in PPV buys if GSP was on the card, so why waste the money.  It was free so we cant really complain, I thought there were some good fights.  And when you say the UFC needs to get better... they're merging with the WEC in January, 135 / 145 lbs fights added to the cards will ensure better fights guaranteed.  I've never been more excited for the sport... Look at the cards lined up for the new year so far... impressive... even the free Fight for the Troops event in January looks awesome!
